==English==

===Etymology===
From the 1939 film ''[[w:The Wizard of Oz (1939 film)|The Wizard of Oz]]'' in which Dorothy states "Toto, I've got a feeling we're not in Kansas anymore."

===Phrase===
'''[[not]] [[in]] [[Kansas]] [[anymore]]'''

# {{idiom}} {{colloquial}} {{USA}} No longer in quiet and comfortable surroundings.  In the [[big city]].
#: ''As soon as I walked into that party, I thought "I'm not in Kansas anymore."''

====Synonyms====
* [[out of one's depth]]